WHO   — The Ouroboros — the serpent eating its tail
WHAT  — The oldest alchemical glyph: matter is one and eternally cyclic — ‘the All is One.’ Drawn beside Maria the Jewess's axiom.
WHERE — ALC · The Great Work  Framework inputs: Alchemy, catalogued by ROOT0  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the Work needed an image for the unity of all matter and the endlessness of transformation.
HOW   — As a drawn emblem encircling the words ἓν τὸ πᾶν — ‘one is the all.’

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  End is beginning — I eat my own tail to say the matter is one, and the Work never truly stops.

